==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[brýne]]

===Pronunciation===
*brīn, /braɪn/, /<tt>braIn</tt>/

===Noun===
'''brine''' (''uncountable'')
1. water saturated or strongly impregnated with salt. 
2. a salt and water solution for pickling. 
3. the sea or ocean. 
4. the water of the sea. 
5. Chem.any saline solution. 

#([[uncountable]])
# Salt [[water]]
:"The ship sank to the briney deep"
:"Do you want the can of tuna in oil or in brine?"

